{"TopicId":141700,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"VTOL","CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-13T03:14:57Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-13T03:14:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2F545522748962116%2Fvideos%2F591456584368732%2F\u0022 style=\u0022height:150px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RizzoTheRat","CreatedById":123362,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-13T11:09:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve seen a few people do that with prop driven models, where the prop is providing enough airflow over the surfaces to control it, but presumably that\u0027s a ducted fan (I\u0027m guessing a model jet wouldn\u0027t be responsive enough and have no sound on my work PC), so how the hell does he control it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"T-Bouw","CreatedById":21500,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-14T15:05:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThrust vectoring is your answer.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thrust_vectoring\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thrust_vectoring\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027ve seen this thing done with a model Mig-29OVT as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe real things couldn\u0027t do that, neither the prop- nor the jet-planes.\u003Cbr\u003E\nStill, pretty impressive although a little weird looking.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-14T19:14:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222630480\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465916705\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002221500\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022T-Bouw\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, T-Bouw said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe real things couldn\u0027t do that, neither the prop- nor the jet-planes.\u003Cbr\u003E\nStill, pretty impressive although a little weird looking.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, they tried.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tail-sitter\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tail-sitter\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-14T21:40:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222630805\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465931655\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, they tried.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tail-sitter\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tail-sitter\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHad an Laythe spaceplane back in 0.9 who worked like this, yes I used stall\u002B parachutes for vertical decent then engine to soft land.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNot an good pilot,\u00A0the ground tend to be bumpy and I wanted an water landing for science.\u003Cbr\u003E\nWorked nice enough.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"T-Bouw","CreatedById":21500,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-15T09:50:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222631009\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465940430\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHad an Laythe spaceplane back in 0.9 who worked like this, yes I used stall\u002B parachutes for vertical decent then engine to soft land.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNot an good pilot,\u00A0the ground tend to be bumpy and I wanted an water landing for science.\u003Cbr\u003E\nWorked nice enough.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh yeah! Did the same thing on Kerbin with an early career plane when I had no wheeled gear unlocked.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI had to flip the thing around and then land on it\u0027s tail.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNeedless to say that it was indeed very hard to do so with the controls getting flipped as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}